Sentencas: Electrochemical performance of composite cathodes consisted of an electron-oxygen-ion mixed conductor, Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (SSC), and a proton conductor, BaCe0.8Sm0.2O3-delta (BCS) was investigated for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with proton-conducing ceramics as the electrolytes.
Titulo: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-BaCe0.8Sm0.2O3-δ composite cathodes for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Interfacial polarization resistance of the composite decreased with SSC content to the minimum at 60 wt.% SSC and then increased.
Titulo: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-BaCe0.8Sm0.2O3-δ composite cathodes for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Firing temperature of the cathodes also affected the resistance, and high performance cathode could be obtained by firing at 1050 degrees C.
Titulo: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-BaCe0.8Sm0.2O3-δ composite cathodes for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The minimum interfacial polarization resistance was 0.21 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C, where powder density of 0.24 W/cm(2) was achieved with humidified hydrogen as the fuel and ambient air as the oxidant.
Titulo: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-BaCe0.8Sm0.2O3-δ composite cathodes for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The low interfacial polarization resistance suggests promise applications of SSC-BCS composites as the cathodes for SOFCs based on proton-conducting electrolytes.
Titulo: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-BaCe0.8Sm0.2O3-δ composite cathodes for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
